---
// This is the "component script" section.
// You can write JavaScript/TypeScript here to fetch data or define variables.
// For a static page like this, it can be empty.
// Importing icons from lucide-icons

import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import BackgroundAbout from "../components/backgrounds/BackgroundAbout.astro";
import ThemeToggle from "../components/ThemeToggle.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Home from "../components/icons/Home.astro";
const pageTitle = "About Me";
---

<BackgroundAbout />
<Layout title={pageTitle} />

<ThemeToggle />
<main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
	<!-- Header Section -->
	<div class="flex mt-12">
		<a href="/" aria-label="Go to Home Page">
			<Home />
		</a>
		<h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold">about</h1>
	</div>
	<hr class="border-gray-700 my-4" />
	<!-- Personal Info Section -->
	<div class="text-left">
		<h2 class="text-lg font-regular">improve and growth</h2>
		<h2 class="text-lg font-regular">faster and better</h2>
		<div class="my-2 text-regular">
			<div>
				<div>
					<h3>Hey, I'm Parkis. Thanks for stopping by.</h3>
					<p class="my-2">
						You could say I'm a Philosophy bachelor who genuinely loves tech. I
						started my journey as a System and Network Admin, getting my hands
						dirty with tools like Mikrotik and Unifi. These days, I've swapped
						that for the world of Business Intelligence and Analytics.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold my-4">How I Stumbled into Data</h3>
					<p>
						I used to be a web developer, managing Linux servers and doing SEO
						for WordPress sites. While I was in the weeds of digital marketing,
						I found the analytics side of things. It was the first time I saw
						how the things I built were actually being measured, and honestly,
						it was a lightbulb moment for me.
					</p>
					<p>
						Seeing the dashboards in Google Analytics and on my own server
						completely changed my perspective. It helped us make a tough call:
						to shut down our own website. We realized the PHP and WordPress
						setup was a huge resource hog, and most of our customers were
						finding us on Instagram and Facebook anyway. It taught me something
						important: whatever I build, it has to actually matter and make a
						real impact.
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold my-4">My Journey and Go-To Tools</h3>
					<p>
						After that, I was hooked. I jumped headfirst into Business
						Intelligence. I realized it's not just about charts and numbersâ€”it's
						about understanding the story behind the data through things like
						Data Modeling and building Data Pipelines.
					</p>
					<p>
						While my main focus is on analytics, I do enjoy coding for data
						pipelines and transformations. I'm really into serverless and
						low-code solutions right now. Here are some of the tools I use
						regularly:
					</p>
					<p class="my-2">
						<strong>Coding:</strong> Python, Astro, Svelte<br />
						<strong>Productivity & BI:</strong> Google Workspace, AppSheet, QField,
						QGIS<br />
						<strong>Platforms:</strong> Cloudflare, SQLite, Geopackage
					</p>

					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold my-4">What I Do</h3>
					<p>
						So that's what I do now! I help people and businesses make better
						decisions by:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside">
						<li class="my-2">
							Figuring out the right data to track based on what they want to
							achieve.
						</li>
						<li class="my-2">
							Pulling that data together from all the different places it lives.
						</li>
						<li class="my-2">
							Setting up smart and simple ways to collect data with tools like
							AppSheet and QField.
						</li>
						<li class="my-2">
							Turning raw data into insights and ideas for improvement with
							dashboards and reports.
						</li>
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="my-2 text-sm">
					<p class="my-2">
						See my solution page to see my past and current work on Business
						Intelligence and Analytics.
					</p>
					<p class="my-2">
						I have so much things to learn, I read when stuck and write when
						overthinking - if you interest, check my digital garden in writing
						section. Its contain my interest and topic im working. Feel free to
						connect with me on social media or email. Maybe we can learn
						together or collaborate on something.
					</p>
				</div>
				<Footer />
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</main>
